The attack occurred on Thursday night near Kinnipadavu Cross, where Shetty was ambushed by armed assailants. Shetty, who had a criminal record and was implicated in the 2022 killing of Mohammed Fazil, succumbed to his injuries after being hospitalized. Police are investigating the motive behind the attack.
title: Mangaluru murder case: 8 arrested in killing of Hindu activist Suhas Shetty

description: Microsoft has surpassed Apple to become the world's most valuable company, boasting a market capitalization of $3.235 trillion, driven by strong cloud and AI demand. Apple's market cap closed at $3.07 trillion, while Nvidia secured the third position at $2.76 trillion. Apple faces headwinds from tariffs, leading to a significant stock decline this year.
title: Microsoft becomes world's most-valuable co with a ‘Trump Tariff' message on Apple

description: Renowned Pakistani Sufi singer Abida Parveen’s Instagram profile is no longer accessible to users in India.This move is part of the ongoing restrictions imposed on several prominent Pakistani celebrities following the recent terror attacks in Pahalgam, India.
title: Pakistani singer Abida Parveen's Instagram account banned amid tensions with Pakistan

description: Delhi-NCR residents and even the IMD were caught off guard by Friday's intense thunderstorm and heavy rain. The IMD's nowcast failed to predict the storm's severity, with Safdarjung recording 60mm of rain in three hours. The confluence of intense heat, moisture from both the Arabian Sea and Bay of Bengal, strong westerlies, and a western disturbance created the potent storm.
title: Delhi caught napping! Rain brings the good, the bad, and the ugly

description: Karnataka Housing Minister Zameer Ahmad Khan declared his readiness to fight against Pakistan, even as a suicide bomber, if permitted by Prime Minister Modi, Amit Shah, and the central government. Khan emphasized his Indian identity and asserted Pakistan's status as an enemy, expressing his willingness to take up arms for the country. He stated his commitment was not a joke.
title: 'If Modi permits, I will go as suicide bomber in war against Pakistan': K'taka min

description: Amid rising tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack, India has withheld the X account of Pakistan's information minister, Attaullah Tarar, after he accused India of planning military action. This action follows a similar block on Pakistan's defense minister's account and a ban on 16 Pakistani YouTube channels for allegedly spreading misinformation.
title: India suspends Pakistan's I&B minister Attaullah Tarar's X account

description: Donald Trump, after joking about becoming Pope, posted an AI-generated image of himself in papal attire on Truth Social, sparking widespread reactions. This occurred as the Catholic Church prepares for a conclave on May 7 to elect a new Pope following Pope Francis's death. Several cardinals, including Parolin, Tagle, Ambongo, Zuppi, and Erdo, are considered potential successors.
title: Make Vatican great again? Trump shares AI image after joking about becoming Pope

description: For nine consecutive days, Pakistan has violated the ceasefire along the Line of Control (LoC), prompting proportionate responses from the Indian Army. The unprovoked small-arms fire targeted areas including Kupwara, Uri, and Akhnoor in J&K. Pakistan has put its armed forces on high alert fearing a military action by India.
title: Pakistan violates ceasefire for 9th day, Indian Army gives prompt response

description: In Baruth, Brandenburg, Red Bull's water extraction plans are facing scrutiny amid climate change concerns. While the mayor emphasizes job creation and sufficient water reserves, environmentalists worry about sustainability and potential contamination. A legal challenge seeks transparency regarding subsidies and water costs, highlighting the tension between economic development and environmental protection in a water-scarce region.
title: Red Bull's plans spark water scarcity fears near Berlin

description: Two years after ethnic conflict erupted in Manipur, thousands remain displaced, struggling with lost livelihoods and uncertain futures. G Kipgen, once a coaching institute owner, now worries about his children's future. Abung, a Meitei businessman, yearns for his home. Despite government efforts, deep insecurity and psychological distress persist among IDPs, with civil society demands and armed groups hindering peace.
title: Two years of Manipur conflict: Thousands wait to go home

description: A tragic stampede at Goa's Sree Lairai Devi temple during the Lairai Zatra festival has claimed at least six lives and injured 60 others. The incident occurred early Saturday morning as thousands of devotees gathered. Chief Minister Pramod Sawant has assured support to the affected families, while PM Narendra Modi has offered central assistance.
title: Watch: Moment when stampede broke out at Goa temple

description: During a commencement speech at the University of Alabama, President Trump addressed his relationship with Elon Musk, offering initial praise followed by a veiled jab. These remarks came shortly after Musk's departure from his advisory role at the White House, marking a shift in their dynamic. Trump's comments highlight the complex interplay between tech leaders, government, and strategic media narratives.
title: Did Donald Trump humiliate Elon Musk in meandering graduation speech

description: A proposal for Delhi University's psychology syllabus has sparked controversy after key topics like the Israel-Palestine conflict, Kashmir issue, and dating app-related suicides were allegedly removed. The committee chair cited reasons such as the resolution of the Kashmir issue and the strength of the Indian family system, leading to accusations of political motivation and unwarranted interference in academic decision-making. A panel has been formed to rework the syllabus.
title: 'Overrepresentation of Western ideas': No Kashmir, Palestine in DU psychology syllabus

description: Top US officials have criticized Germany's decision to label the AfD as a right-wing extremist entity, with JD Vance likening it to rebuilding the Berlin Wall and Marco Rubio denouncing it as tyranny. Germany's Foreign Ministry defended the move as necessary to protect the constitution and counter right-wing extremism, citing historical lessons.
title: US criticizes Germany for labeling AfD 'extremist'

description: Tejashwi Yadav, RJD leader, urged Prime Minister Modi to reconsider the reservation cap after the caste census data is available, emphasizing the need for social justice and proportional representation. He highlighted the potential for the census to reveal significant underrepresentation of OBCs and EBCs, advocating for inclusivity in both political representation and the private sector, which benefits from public resources.
title: 'Caste census merely first step': Tejashwi writes to PM Modi, bats for private quota

description: A Russian drone strike, utilizing Iranian-made Shahed drones, targeted Kharkiv, Ukraine's second-largest city, injuring over 40 people, including an 11-year-old girl. President Zelenskyy condemned the attack on residential areas and civilian infrastructure, emphasizing the lack of military targets. He urged world leaders to bolster Ukraine's air defenses, while a separate Russian strike on Zaporizhzhia wounded over 20.
title: Russia strikes Ukraine's Kharkiv with Iranian-made drones, 40 injured

description: While home advantage is significant in many sports, its impact in the IPL is debatable. Factors like familiarity and crowd support are often nullified by diverse team compositions. Despite strong home records of teams like CSK and MI, recent seasons show a decline in home wins, sparking debate about pitch conditions and the extent of home advantage in the league.
title: From Chepauk to Eden Gardens: Does home advantage even exist in the IPL?

description: Prince Harry's recent legal challenge regarding his UK security arrangements was unsuccessful, potentially leading to significant legal expenses. Despite this setback, his estimated net worth stands at $60 million, bolstered by inheritances from Princess Diana and the Queen Mother.
title: How does 'Spare' royal family member earn after leaving royal fold?

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru's crucial IPL 2025 match against Chennai Super Kings faces a rain threat, potentially impacting RCB's top-two aspirations. Bengaluru has experienced incessant rain, with a 70% chance of continued showers on match day. CSK's training was disrupted on Friday, while RCB's session was cut short due to heavy downpour.
title: IPL 2025: Will rain play spoilsport in RCB vs CSK in Bengaluru?

description: Shubman Gill's controversial run-out dismissal sparked a heated exchange with umpires during Gujarat Titans' 38-run victory over Sunrisers Hyderabad. Gill, visibly frustrated with the DRS decision, voiced his emotions after being given out. Despite the drama, GT's dominant batting performance, highlighted by minimal dot balls, propelled them to a crucial win, strengthening their playoff aspirations.
title: Shubman Gill opens up on heated umpire exchange: 'There are bound to be …’

description: The US Justice Department is pushing for a breakup of Google's advertising technology business, following a ruling that Google illegally monopolized parts of the digital ad market. The proposal targets Google's ad exchange and publisher tools, aiming to increase competition. Google opposes the plan, arguing it's impractical and would harm security and privacy protections.
title: US govt to court: Not breaking Google’s ad tech business is ‘frankly, too dangerous’

description: A tragic stampede at the Shree Lairai Zatra festival in Goa's Shirgao village resulted in the deaths of six people and injuries to at least 30 others. Health officials confirmed the fatalities and reported that several of the injured are in critical condition, requiring specialized treatment at Goa Medical College. The state government has initiated an emergency response, providing medical assistance and closely monitoring the situation as authorities investigate the cause of the incident.
title: 6 dead, 60 injured in stampede at Lairai Zatra in Goa

description: Jeff Bezos revealed that securing Amazon's initial $1 million was his toughest challenge, requiring 60 pitches to angel investors in 1995. He sold 20% of the company for a $5 million valuation, cautioning investors about a 70% risk of loss.
title: Amazon founder Jeff Bezos on the 'Hardest test' he has ever faced

description: Australians have cast their votes in a tightly contested national election, choosing between incumbent Prime Minister Anthony Albanese and opposition leader Peter Dutton. Key issues include the rising cost of living and the impact of US tariffs. Most opinion polls in the days before the election suggested that Albanese’s Labor Party was likely to win a second term in government.
title: Australia elections: Who's running, why is Trump a factor; all you need to know

description: Mika Singh addressed the controversy surrounding his ban for performing in Pakistan after the 2016 Uri attack, highlighting perceived double standards in the industry regarding cross-border collaborations. He pointed out that while others engage in similar projects without facing backlash, he was targeted. The ban on Pakistani artists in India, triggered by terror attacks, continues to impact cultural exchanges.
title: Mika Singh reflects on ban he faced for performing in Pakistan after Uri attack

description: Charanjit Singh Channi, a Congress MP, ignited controversy by questioning the veracity of India's surgical strikes in Pakistan, stating he found no evidence of them. The BJP strongly condemned Channi's remarks, accusing him of disrespecting the armed forces and politicizing national security.
title: 'Nobody came to know': Congress' Channi questions surgical strike; BJP hits back

description: A tragic stampede at the Lairai Devi temple in Goa during the Shree Devi Lairai jatra has resulted in the death of at least six people and injuries to over fifteen others. Authorities have initiated an emergency response, with the injured being shifted to nearby hospitals. The cause of the stampede is currently unknown, and investigations are underway as the chief minister assesses the situation.
title: Thousands gathered for local festival: How did the Goa stampede occur?
US govt wants Indian national Suri’s deportation suit shifted; judge pushes back

description: Meta and Microsoft are venturing into AI companionship to combat the growing loneliness epidemic, as highlighted by Mark Zuckerberg's vision of AI friends. These AI companions aim to provide emotional support and fill the gap in meaningful connections, addressing the decline in close friendships. However, challenges remain in creating empathetic AI and navigating ethical concerns about dependency and privacy.
title: Mark Zuckerberg says Meta has a plan to beat ‘the loneliness epidemic’

description: The Trump administration ended duty-free access for low-value shipments from China and Hong Kong, effective May 2, 2025. This closes a loophole used by e-commerce giants and illicit goods traffickers, potentially raising prices for American consumers. The move mirrors India's 2020 crackdown on Chinese 'gift' imports evading taxes.
title: Trump tariffs hurt Chinese shopping sites like India’s 2020 ban

description: Ajay Devgn's 'Raid 2' has made a strong start at the Indian box office, earning over Rs. 30 crore in its first two days. The film, directed by Raj Kumar Gupta, opened with Rs. 19.25 crore on Thursday, boosted by a partial holiday and franchise popularity. While Day 2 saw a drop to Rs. 11.
title: Raid 2 box office day 2: Ajay Devgn’s crime drama mints over Rs 11 crore

description: Mumbai police filed a case against Ajaz Khan and Rajkumar Pandey for alleged obscene content in their web show, 'House Arrest'. A Bajrang Dal member filed the complaint. The National Commission for Women has summoned Ullu App CEO Vibhu Agarwal and Khan. The show has been removed from the Ullu app.
title: Ullu app CEO booked over ‘intimate positions’ on reality show 'House Arrest'

description: Tension escalated in Canacona as Pakistani flags were discovered painted on roads at key locations early Friday, raising concerns about potential communal disharmony. Goa assembly speaker Ramesh Tawadkar filed a police complaint, urging a thorough investigation. Locals questioned the effectiveness of night patrolling, while community leaders appealed for calm. Police are reviewing CCTV footage to identify the culprits.
title: Pakistan flags painted on roads spark tension in Goa
